The most amazing Indian food in Manhattan. Forget little India and go to Harlem for this delicious encounter. My husband and I love the intimate space, the cozy factor of the ambiance, the outstanding service, scrumptious meals, and great pricing! So much to love about this amazing restaurant. We discovered it about 3 weeks ago and have already become regulars; the staff knows our faces and our order! Not a single complaint or shortcoming at this place. Absolutely amazing work all around. If anyone leaves less than 5 stars they are delirious. Not to mention the same meal (of lesser quality) downtown is at least double (if not triple) the price.  Dishes not to miss: -chicken tikka salad (the mango mayo dressing is TO DIE FOR and there’s actually a good serving of chicken in there!) -chicken korma (perfect balance of sweet and savory) -gulab jamun (most amazing soft sweet warm fluffy balls)
Only got delivery, but it was good. Especially the vegetarian options. The methi matar malai is a standout. The veg tika Masala was a little too sweet and watery.

I definitely encourage everyone in the neighborhood to try Delhi Masala if they are not accustomed to Indian cuisine. Me and my girlfriend went there Saturday late lunch and we really enjoyed our first experience there. My favorite Indian dish is saag paneer just because I can't compare it to anything else veggie so I ordered it and it didnt disappoint. At first I thought it looked dry but it's just really balanced when you eat it with garlic naan. My favorite plate however was the Chicken Vindaloo because it has the perfect amount of hot. The chicken was extremely tender and the sauce was spot on from the color to the thickness. I am very excited this is right around the corner from 125

Delhi Masala has a few unique dishes on the menu that aren't very common such as Murg Madras and Kerala Pepper Chicken.  Prices and portions are standard for Indian food in NYC.  If you get a chance to dine in, the venue has charming copper ceiling tiles and exposed brick.

My wife and I stopped off at Delhi Masala for the first time one Sunday afternoon for an early dinner.  I go the Butter Chicken and my wife got some kind of vegetable rice dish.  We were extremely pleased with both of  our meals.  My Butter Chicken was the perfect combination of savory and spicey.  The service was great - attentive but not overbearing.  The atmosphere was quite nice as well.  And, they had Taj Mahal beer - what more could you ask for in an indian restaurant.  We use to head down from Harlem to a place on Greenwhich Street to get our indian fix.  After discovering Delhi Masala we now only have to walk a few blocks.  Very happy about that.
